---
import FeatureCard from './FeatureCard.astro';
---

<section id="features">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="kicker" data-reveal>What it does</p>
    <h2 data-reveal>Capture it. Ask it. Remember it.</h2>
    <p class="lead" data-reveal>Everything a new hire needs runs in one small floating window you can resize, dim, or tuck away during any onboarding meeting.</p>
    <div class="grid" data-reveal-group>
      <FeatureCard icon="🎙️" title="Capture onboarding meetings">
        System audio and your mic, transcribed live and labelled by speaker — on-device Apple Speech,
        no cloud required. Nothing in those first 1:1s gets lost.
      </FeatureCard>
      <FeatureCard icon="✦" title="In-the-moment answers">
        Ask "how do we do X here?" mid-meeting and get a tight answer in a dedicated pane — drawn from
        what's being said and the context you've fed it. No interrupting your lead.
      </FeatureCard>
      <FeatureCard icon="📸" title="Snapshot &amp; read">
        Grab a region of the screen and OCR it instantly — entirely on-device with Apple Vision. Pull a
        diagram, dashboard, or internal doc straight into the copilot.
      </FeatureCard>
      <FeatureCard icon="🧠" title="Tribal knowledge, captured">
        The undocumented "we always do it this way" gets written down as it's spoken — so the answer is
        ready the next time anyone needs it, not stuck in someone's head.
      </FeatureCard>
      <FeatureCard icon="🔒" title="Private &amp; BYOK">
        Transcription and OCR happen on your Mac. The copilot runs on <em>your</em> AI keys — nothing is
        shared, each session is isolated. Onboarding conversations stay internal.
      </FeatureCard>
      <FeatureCard icon="⌨️" title="Global hotkeys">
        Surface an answer and stop the capture without leaving your call — <code>⌃⌥A</code> and
        <code>⌃⌥S</code>, from anywhere.
      </FeatureCard>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 18px;
    margin-top: 44px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
